condition.narrative: For the purposes of implementing Part 2(c) of the Project, the Recipient not later than 30 days after the Effectiveness Date shallprepare an manual for the NFPE (NFPE Implementation Manual). (FA Schedule 2.I.C.2)

Not later than one month after the Effective Date, the Recipient shall establish, and thereafter maintain throughout Projectimplementation the following units: a Project Implementation Unit within MCTESTP (MCTESTP PCU), responsible for overseeingday-to-day implementation of Project activities, including fiduciary management, monitoring and evaluation, reporting as well asthe compiling of all data, information and evidence of achieving the PBCs; and (b) a unit within ANEP (ANEP PCU), responsible forthe oversight of Parts 2 and selected activities under Part 3 of the Project, all under terms of reference, staffing withqualifications, experience, resources and terms of reference satisfactory to the Association as well as the necessary funds. (FA -Schedule 2.I.A.1)

The Recipient shall prepare not later than 30 days after the Effective Date and thereafter ensure that the Project is implementedin accordance with the provisions of a manual satisfactory to the Association (“Project Implementation Manual or PIM”). (FASchedule 2.I.C.1)

The Recipient, not later than 60 days after the Effective Date, shall create and thereafter maintain a Project Steering Committee,with composition and terms of reference acceptable to the Association, chaired by the Permanent Secretary of MCTESTP and includingrepresentatives of ANEP, MoF, and other key stakeholders, with the responsibility of guiding and coordinating the implementation ofthe Project. (FA- Schedule 2.I.A.4)
